attention - adds howard, campbell remarks ///
environment minister ian campbell said japan risks damaging its reputation in the eyes of most australians if it persists with plans to hunt humpback whales .
prime minister john howard intervened personally , writing to his japanese counterpart junichiro koizumi at the weekend to urge tokyo to reconsider its position on whaling .
humane society international was denied permission by australia 's federal court to sue japanese whaling company kyodo senpaku for allegedly killing around 400 minke whales in antarctic waters the australian government has declared a whale sanctuary .
